# Portal Registry Data Mismatch Resolution

## Summary
Resolved the UI/component naming mismatch preventing the Registry from loading in the Portal frontend.

## Changes Made

### [registry.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/registry.js)
- Renamed from `regions.js`
- Class renamed from `ZgetRegions` → [ZgetRegistry](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/registry.js#3-213)
- Custom element registered as `zget-registry`

### [app.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/app.js)
- Updated import: `./regions.js` → [./registry.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/registry.js)
- Updated lazy-load check and nav items to use `registry` view name
- Updated view pane ID to `view-registry`

### [service-worker.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/service-worker.js)
- Bumped `APP_SHELL_CACHE` from `v1` → `v2` to invalidate stale caches

## Verification

Browser verification confirmed:
- ✅ Sidebar navigation present (📀 Vault, 🚀 Activity, 🌐 Registry, ⚙️ Settings)
- ✅ Registry loads with dense grid of 1,600+ site chips
- ✅ No console errors (no 404s for [registry.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/registry.js))

